WEBVTT

00:25.942 --> 00:28.944
** [ Drums Beating ]

00:50.717 --> 01:19.995
*[ [ Continues ]

02:11.297 --> 02:13.215
*[ [ Ends ]

02:13.299 --> 02:15.342
** [ Flute: Somber Melody ]

02:25.895 --> 02:27.896
*[ [ Continues ]

03:06.436 --> 03:08.437
*[ [ Ends ]

03:08.521 --> 03:12.191
- Have you fallen asleep?
- [ French Accent ] Oh, I'm sorry.

03:12.275 --> 03:15.569
- I thinkyou must be in love or something.
- [ Footsteps Approaching ]

03:18.740 --> 03:21.283
Why does the old bitch pick on me?

03:23.036 --> 03:26.371
That's the second time this week. I nearly
told her what she could do with thejob.

03:26.456 --> 03:28.999
Hey, you asleep?

03:29.083 --> 03:31.001
That's what I asked her.

03:31.085 --> 03:33.754
She wants me to stay till 7:00 again.

03:47.560 --> 03:50.187
[ Woman ]
What polish are you putting on?

03:50.271 --> 03:53.982
- The usual one, madame.
- Oh, I'm fed up with it.

03:54.067 --> 03:56.318
I feel like a change.

03:56.402 --> 04:00.489
- Uh, give me Revlon's Fire and Ice.
- Oh, I'll go and get it.

04:05.787 --> 04:08.121
[ Whirring ]

04:15.213 --> 04:17.214
- [ Clicks ]
- [ Hair Dryer Whirring ]

04:17.298 --> 04:19.632
[ Chattering ]

04:23.054 --> 04:25.055
Madame Denise?

04:26.182 --> 04:30.143
Madame Denise,
Mrs. Rendlesham wants Revlon Fire and Ice.

04:31.187 --> 04:33.313
I don't think there's any left.

04:35.108 --> 04:37.109
[ Chattering ]

04:40.989 --> 04:43.991
Put this on.
She'll never know the difference.

04:44.075 --> 04:46.743
** [ Flute Ensemble:Jazz ]

04:55.003 --> 04:57.004
[ Heels Clicking On Sidewalk ]

05:24.115 --> 05:26.116
*[ [ Continues ]

05:33.750 --> 05:36.209
Hello, darling.
How about a bit ofthe other, then?

05:36.294 --> 05:38.295
[ Bus Engine Roars ]

05:41.299 --> 05:43.300
[ Chattering ]

05:45.094 --> 05:47.095
[ Plates Clattering ]

05:50.808 --> 05:52.809
*[ [ Continues ]

05:59.650 --> 06:01.568
*[ [ Ends ]

06:02.570 --> 06:04.571
[ No Audible Dialogue ]

06:25.843 --> 06:27.844
[ Sighs ]

06:35.853 --> 06:38.355
You can't eat stuff like this.

06:38.439 --> 06:41.233
Come on.
I'll take you to Wheeler's. Okay?

06:43.486 --> 06:45.445
I have to get back.

06:45.530 --> 06:47.906
Oh, we can have a —
we can have a quick meal.

06:49.784 --> 06:51.785
Come on.

06:54.664 --> 06:57.207
I can't. "ll be late.

06:57.291 --> 06:59.960
Well,just —just one thing.

07:00.044 --> 07:02.045
No?

07:04.632 --> 07:06.133
I can't.

07:20.898 --> 07:22.941
[ Sighs ]

07:23.025 --> 07:25.152
Well, good-bye.

07:25.236 --> 07:28.196
Well,just a —just a minute.
What about tonight?

07:29.323 --> 07:31.741
I'm sorry, but I'm busy tonight.

07:32.785 --> 07:35.245
You really make me feel wanted.

07:35.329 --> 07:37.414
Who's the lucky boy?

07:37.498 --> 07:40.292
I'm having dinner with my sister.

07:40.376 --> 07:42.794
Is she a good cook?

07:42.879 --> 07:45.505
[ Chuckles ]
I don't know. I never thought about it.

07:46.507 --> 07:49.801
Well, at least it can't be
any worse than fish and chips.

07:49.886 --> 07:51.887
[ Chuckles ]

07:53.014 --> 07:55.432
I think we are having rabbit.

07:55.516 --> 07:57.601
Rabbit? Oh.

07:57.685 --> 08:00.020
I thought they'd all been killed off.

08:01.022 --> 08:04.566
- No. She has a friend —
- A rabbit?

08:04.650 --> 08:06.860
No, I think the friend has rabbits.

08:08.070 --> 08:10.864
Poor bunny.
Well, what about tomorrow?

08:12.241 --> 08:14.868
- Tomorrow?
- Yeah. Let's have dinner tomorrow.

08:14.952 --> 08:18.538
I'll meet you at the Hoop and Toy.
You know, the pub along there.

08:18.623 --> 08:21.458
About, uh, 7:00?

08:25.880 --> 08:27.881
[ Chattering ]

08:31.344 --> 08:33.345
[ Engine Starts ]

08:38.433 --> 08:41.436
** [ Flute: Somber Melody ]

08:53.741 --> 08:55.742
*[ [ Fades ]

08:57.620 --> 08:59.538
- Hello.
- Hello.

08:59.622 --> 09:02.666
Come along boy. Walkies. Walkies.

09:02.750 --> 09:04.918
- [ Doorbell Rings ]
- Walkies.

09:07.255 --> 09:09.256
[ Footsteps Approaching ]

09:09.340 --> 09:11.341
[ Elevator Whirring ]

09:20.643 --> 09:23.144
[ Plates Clinking ]

09:30.987 --> 09:32.988
[ Chattering, Laughter In Distance ]

09:34.740 --> 09:37.742
[ Chattering, Laughter ]

09:38.786 --> 09:41.121
[ Woman ]
Have a good day?

09:42.164 --> 09:44.791
- Darling?
- Yes.

10:45.519 --> 10:48.396
- How was work?
- All right.

10:49.690 --> 10:52.442
[ Sighs ]
It's close today.

10:52.526 --> 10:56.529
- Are you still going away?
- Oh, darling, please don't start that again.

10:58.282 --> 11:01.785
- How long are you going for?
- I've told you.

11:01.869 --> 11:03.828
- Fortnight?
- Mind.

11:05.289 --> 11:07.290
How long?

11:08.668 --> 11:10.794
Ten or 1 2 days.

11:10.878 --> 11:12.879
No more than that?

11:15.549 --> 11:17.467
[ Chuckles ]

11:17.551 --> 11:19.886
I heard such a funny story
on the news this evening.

11:19.970 --> 11:22.931
Does he have to leave his things
in the bathroom?

11:23.015 --> 11:25.934
The minister of health—
What's his name?

11:26.018 --> 11:28.353
He found eels coming out of his sink.

11:28.437 --> 11:31.481
It was on the television.
Even the announcer was laughing.

11:31.565 --> 11:34.234
Why does he put his toothbrush in my glass?

11:37.238 --> 11:39.739
Carol, please.

11:53.003 --> 11:55.839
We must get this crack mended.

11:55.923 --> 11:58.591
- What?
- [ Doorbell Rings ]

12:06.934 --> 12:09.352
[ Door Closes ]

12:09.437 --> 12:11.187
- Hello.
- Hello.

12:11.272 --> 12:14.524
You're early.
I didn't expect you for hours.

12:14.608 --> 12:16.860
I couldn't live without you
for another minute.

12:16.944 --> 12:21.030
Idiot. Anyway, you said 8:30.
I haven't even started yet.

12:21.115 --> 12:23.199
There's a marvelous story
in this evening's paper.

12:23.284 --> 12:26.202
- It takes at least one hour.
- Huh?

12:26.287 --> 12:28.455
Your rabbit.
I'm cooking it.

12:28.539 --> 12:33.543
Look. "Bring to the boil. Skim and allow to
simmer slowly for one and a half hours."

12:33.627 --> 12:36.171
Yes. Well, we'll eat out tonight.
I'll take you out.

12:36.255 --> 12:39.257
- Here. Look. Read that.
- [ Bell Clanging ]

12:40.259 --> 12:43.219
Oh, I know that.
I saw it on television.

12:43.304 --> 12:46.389
- That bloody bell.
- [ Clanging Continues ]

12:48.100 --> 12:50.935
Eels.
[ Chuckles ]

12:51.020 --> 12:53.021
Pity it wasn't lobster though.

12:53.105 --> 12:57.567
You never give me a chance
to show you what a good cook I am.

12:57.651 --> 13:00.695
- Well you can tell me over dinner.
- [ Clanging Continues ]

13:00.780 --> 13:04.240
You'd think they'd have something better
to do than clang away like that all the time.

13:04.325 --> 13:07.744
Hmm. It's worse when they start
doing it at midnight.

13:07.828 --> 13:11.414
I wonder what they ring it for anyway.
Perhaps they have wild parties.

13:11.499 --> 13:14.918
- Maybe they'll invite me sometime.
- [ Chuckles ]

13:15.002 --> 13:16.920
[ Clanging Stops ]

13:17.004 --> 13:20.507
Go and put your best bib and tucker on.
I feel like a spree.

13:22.551 --> 13:24.928
Ah.

13:25.012 --> 13:27.555
The beautiful younger sister.

13:27.640 --> 13:29.641
Comment ca va?

13:37.024 --> 13:39.025
I thought you were eating in.

13:42.571 --> 13:44.572
Aren't you going to have dinner?

13:45.825 --> 13:49.202
Yes. I'm going to have dinner.

13:50.788 --> 13:53.832
- But not here.
- No.

13:53.916 --> 13:55.917
Not here.

13:56.919 --> 13:58.837
[ Sighs ]

13:58.921 --> 14:01.256
Pass me that brush, will you?
There's a love.

14:06.220 --> 14:09.639
Just because I go out once,
there's no need to start sulking.

14:09.723 --> 14:13.518
- I'm not sulking.
- Hmm. Well, you're not exactly smiling.

14:15.271 --> 14:17.814
Come on. You're not going in
for the Miss World competition.

14:17.898 --> 14:19.524
[ Elevator Whirs ]

14:20.901 --> 14:23.111
Will we go and see
the Leaning Tower of Pisa?

14:23.195 --> 14:25.196
I don't think Cinderella likes me.

14:25.281 --> 14:27.198
- Cinderella?
- The little sister.

14:27.283 --> 14:29.617
Ah' don't be silly.

14:29.702 --> 14:32.078
Well are we going to see
the Leaning Tower of Pisa?

14:32.162 --> 14:34.247
She's a bit strung-up, isn't she?

14:35.583 --> 14:37.750
- She's just sensitive. That's all.
- [ Chuckles ]

14:37.835 --> 14:40.879
You can say that again.
She should see a doctor.

14:41.881 --> 14:43.798
- What do you mean?
- Nothing, nothing, nothing.

14:43.883 --> 14:46.467
- No. You tell me what you meant by that.
- Nothing. Let's forget it.

14:46.552 --> 14:49.888
You want to see the Leaning Tower of Pisa,
we'll see the bloody thing. Now let's relax.

14:50.014 --> 14:53.600
- We're going to dinner aren't we?
- Don't always change the subject
when you start talking like that. You hear?

14:54.810 --> 14:56.811
[ Water Dripping ]

15:09.700 --> 15:11.701
[ Dripping Continues ]

15:14.788 --> 15:16.789
[ Elevator Whirring ]

15:29.762 --> 15:31.763
[ Whirring Stops ]

15:32.806 --> 15:34.807
[ Clangs ]

15:42.483 --> 15:44.400
[ Woman ]
Come along, boy. Din-din.

15:44.485 --> 15:46.778
Time for din-din.

15:46.862 --> 15:49.280
Come along, boy. Lovely din-din.

15:54.745 --> 15:56.746
[ Ticking ]

16:07.007 --> 16:09.008
[ Ticking Continues ]

16:19.937 --> 16:21.938
[ Dog Barking In Distance ]

16:27.528 --> 16:29.028
[ Barking Stops ]

16:36.078 --> 16:38.079
[ Vehicle Passing ]

17:31.675 --> 17:33.676
[ Clock Ticking ]

17:40.476 --> 17:43.978
- [ Sister Laughing ]
- [ Man ] Oh, come — [ Indistinct ]

17:44.063 --> 17:46.022
[ Laughing Continues ]

17:46.106 --> 17:54.072
[ Ticking Continues ]

17:59.244 --> 18:02.789
[ Sister Clearing Throat ]

18:02.873 --> 18:05.374
[ Ticking Continues ]

18:09.421 --> 18:12.006
[ Sister Breathing Heavily ]

18:16.345 --> 18:19.514
[ Moaning ]

18:24.478 --> 18:26.479
[ Ticking Continues ]

18:29.274 --> 18:57.718
[ Moaning Continues ]

19:03.183 --> 19:05.184
[ Ticking Continues ]

19:07.855 --> 19:10.940
[ Moaning Intensifies ]

19:15.988 --> 19:17.989
Oh!

19:20.492 --> 19:22.493
[ Moaning Softly ]

19:25.372 --> 19:27.582
[ Sighs ]

19:27.666 --> 19:29.625
Mmm.

19:29.710 --> 19:31.711
[ Sighs ]

19:31.795 --> 19:33.796
[ Ticking Continues ]

19:38.218 --> 19:41.262
- [ Plates Clattering ]
- [ Birds Chirping ]

20:37.277 --> 20:38.861
[ Gasps ]

20:39.863 --> 20:41.864
I'm sorry.

20:44.451 --> 20:46.452
[ Clock Ticking ]

21:07.140 --> 21:09.141
[ Plates Clattering ]

21:13.188 --> 21:15.690
Oh, look. I've got to run.
I've left something at the flat.

21:15.774 --> 21:17.733
Well aren't you going to drop me off?

21:17.818 --> 21:19.777
I've got no time.

21:19.861 --> 21:23.531
Mmm. That's bloody hot.
NoW you —you'll have to take a cab.

21:24.533 --> 21:26.617
Uh, here.

21:28.745 --> 21:31.080
Oh, here. Are you —
Am I gonna see you tonight?

21:31.164 --> 21:33.082
Um —

21:33.166 --> 21:35.084
I-I'll ring you, hmm?

21:35.168 --> 21:37.169
I'll ring you.

21:41.466 --> 21:44.051
[ Elevator Clicks ]

21:44.136 --> 21:46.721
[ Elevator Door Closes ]

21:46.805 --> 21:48.806
[ Elevator Whirring ]

21:54.855 --> 21:56.981
[ Door Opens ]

21:57.065 --> 21:59.191
[ Footsteps Approaching ]

21:59.276 --> 22:01.736
Hello, darling.
How did you sleep?

22:01.820 --> 22:04.238
All right.

22:04.323 --> 22:06.991
Is he going to stay here every night?

22:07.075 --> 22:09.076
[ Airplane Passing Overhead ]

22:18.170 --> 22:20.379
I really don't think it's any concern ofyours.

22:22.215 --> 22:26.052
- [ Phone Rings ]
- He's married though.

22:27.471 --> 22:32.391
- Darling, it's my affair.
- [ Ringing Continues ]

22:37.647 --> 22:40.691
We all have to lead
our own lives in the end, you know.

22:40.776 --> 22:42.777
[ Ringing Continues ]

22:43.904 --> 22:46.822
Well just don't stand around like that.
Go and answer the phone.

22:46.907 --> 22:48.908
Can't you see I'm busy?

22:50.035 --> 22:52.036
[ Ringing Continues ]

22:55.290 --> 22:57.208
- Hello?
- [ Man ] Miss Ledoux?

22:57.292 --> 22:58.292
Yes.

22:58.377 --> 23:01.003
How much longer are you going to
keep me waiting for the rent?

23:01.088 --> 23:04.090
Oh. You want my sister.

23:04.174 --> 23:07.343
- Ah. I suppose she's out.
- No, no. She's here.

23:07.427 --> 23:09.637
- [ Footsteps Approaching ]
-Just a moment.

23:10.847 --> 23:12.807
- Who is it?
- The landlord.

23:12.891 --> 23:15.476
Oh, damn. He would ring up today.

23:18.605 --> 23:20.689
- Hello, yes?
- Miss Ledoux?

23:20.774 --> 23:23.442
- Look. I'm terribly sorry —
- I bet you are.

23:23.527 --> 23:26.362
- Now look. How much longer
are you going to keep me waiting?
- I promise —

23:26.446 --> 23:30.533
- I've had your promises before.
- I promise you'll have the money tomorrow.

23:30.617 --> 23:33.369
That's what you said a fortnight ago.

23:33.453 --> 23:35.371
You'll have the money tomorrow without fail.

23:35.455 --> 23:38.916
- Look. 'fyou're not going to play fair by —
- My sister will bring it round to you.

23:39.000 --> 23:41.001
- [ Man ] Not you?
- N-No.

23:41.086 --> 23:43.003
I'm going away on holiday.

23:43.088 --> 23:45.714
[ Man ] Now look Miss Ledoux.
This time I've had just about —

23:45.799 --> 23:47.842
She'll bring it round to you tomorrow.
I promise.

23:47.926 --> 23:50.052
She better, Miss Ledoux.
That's all I can say.

23:50.137 --> 23:52.513
[ Dial Tone ]

23:52.597 --> 23:56.475
[ Grumbles ] Just the sound
of his voice makes my flesh creep.

23:56.560 --> 23:59.145
Money, money money.
That's all he ever thinks about.

24:00.772 --> 24:03.190
Good heavens.
I shall be late again.

24:13.410 --> 24:16.412
*[ [ Piano: Scales ]

24:41.521 --> 24:43.522
*[ [ Continues ]

25:14.137 --> 25:16.138
[ Blow Dryers Whirring ]

25:16.223 --> 25:18.224
[ Chattering ]

25:22.229 --> 25:25.022
- Is Bridget about?
- Oh, she's downstairs.

25:25.106 --> 25:27.107
Oh.

25:28.360 --> 25:30.361
[ Sobbing ]

25:32.030 --> 25:35.407
[ Pigeons Cooing ]

25:36.493 --> 25:39.119
Bridget.

25:39.204 --> 25:41.580
What's the matter?

25:41.665 --> 25:44.416
- Nothing.
- Tell me.

25:44.501 --> 25:46.502
[ Sniffles ]
Nothing.

25:47.629 --> 25:51.966
Just bloody men.
Promise you the earth, and then —

25:53.093 --> 25:56.387
- Oh, I could cut my throat.
- Don't talk like that.

26:01.893 --> 26:04.395
I thought this one was different.

26:05.647 --> 26:08.274
- Did he —
- Oh, he was a pig. Forget him.

26:08.358 --> 26:11.652
[ Sniffles ]
Oh. Look at my eyes.

26:11.736 --> 26:13.946
[ Woman On P.A. ]
Will Miss Bridget please come to the salon.

26:14.030 --> 26:16.782
Mrs. Prendergast has arrived.

26:16.866 --> 26:19.827
I'll tell you the sordid details later.

26:21.830 --> 26:24.748
Oh, why are they so filthy?

26:26.293 --> 26:28.711
Don't be upset.

26:28.795 --> 26:31.964
[ Woman On P.A. ] Will Miss Bridget
please come to the salon right away.

27:03.121 --> 27:05.998
** [Jazz Ensemble ]

27:46.039 --> 27:48.040
[ Horn Honks ]

27:48.124 --> 27:50.250
*[ [ Continues ]

28:40.510 --> 28:42.553
- [ Man ] Cheerio then.
- [ Man #2 ] See you later.

28:52.105 --> 28:54.022
*[ [ Ends ]

28:54.107 --> 28:56.734
[ Speaking, Garbled ]

29:01.072 --> 29:03.031
- You'rejoking.
- No. You should have seen them.

29:03.116 --> 29:06.034
They went for each other like those
women wrestlers in Hamburg.

29:06.119 --> 29:09.329
One, a big lady with bloody great charlies,
tried to claw the other girl's face.

29:09.414 --> 29:12.541
Got her fist right down her throat.
Two pints of bitter, please.

29:12.625 --> 29:14.376
- [ Bartenders ] Two pints sir?
- [ Man ] Lesbians?

29:14.461 --> 29:17.713
NoW no. They both fancied the same bloke.
' should have his luck.

29:17.797 --> 29:20.466
And then they started in with their teeth,
rolling about on the floor.

29:20.550 --> 29:24.428
It was like a madhouse. And I was
the only mug who tried to prevent them.

29:24.512 --> 29:26.555
I ought to have my head examined.

29:26.639 --> 29:28.849
I wouldn't have minded seeing it.

29:28.933 --> 29:30.559
Feel free, anytime.

29:30.643 --> 29:32.728
- I ended up —
- [ Man ] Thankyou.

29:32.812 --> 29:35.105
my coat torn,
my shirt covered with blood.

29:35.190 --> 29:37.900
Ifyou like that sort ofthing,
I'll introduce you to my cousin.

29:37.984 --> 29:40.444
- She's a black belt.
- Black belt?

29:43.573 --> 29:45.491
How did you get on?

29:46.659 --> 29:48.744
- What?
- [ Man #2 ] What's your cousin like?

29:48.828 --> 29:52.414
- [ Man #1 ] Well how did you get on
with Little Miss Muffet?
- [ Man #2 ] She sounds fun.

29:52.499 --> 29:55.918
- When?
- [ Man #1 ] Well, I thought
you were taking her out to dinner.

29:56.002 --> 29:57.544
[ Man #2 ]
Your cousin — what's she like?

29:57.629 --> 29:59.671
Is that the right time?

29:59.756 --> 30:03.383
- NoW sir.
- Oh, come on.
Fill us in with the gripping details.

30:03.468 --> 30:07.179
The gripping details are
that she had dinnerwith her sister.

30:08.348 --> 30:10.641
Well maybe you should try the sister.

30:33.206 --> 30:35.207
[ Footsteps Approaching ]

30:42.048 --> 30:44.299
Are you playing hard to get?

30:44.384 --> 30:46.301
I've been waiting over an hour.

30:46.386 --> 30:48.387
Wh — What for?

30:49.848 --> 30:51.807
Well not for Christmas.

30:51.891 --> 30:55.227
We made a date. Remember?
We're having supper tonight.

30:55.311 --> 30:57.396
Oh, I forgot.

30:58.898 --> 31:00.899
Oh.

31:04.237 --> 31:07.656
Well next time you forget,
maybe you'll let me know.

31:07.740 --> 31:09.741
It's not that but —

31:14.914 --> 31:16.832
Are you all right?

31:16.916 --> 31:18.876
You look —

31:18.960 --> 31:21.753
I don't know.
You look sort of— sort offunny.

31:22.755 --> 31:25.007
I don't feel —

31:25.091 --> 31:28.093
I mean, I don't know.

31:30.138 --> 31:33.515
Oh well anyway come on. Now I've
found you, let's — let's go and eat something.

31:33.600 --> 31:36.518
- I'm starving.
- But it's too late.

31:39.522 --> 31:42.357
Look. Have — Have you been
fired or something?

31:42.442 --> 31:44.443
** [ Rhythmic Clicking ]

31:47.322 --> 31:50.532
All right. Come on.
I'll take you home. Come on.

31:50.617 --> 31:52.618
** [ Clicking Continues ]

31:56.623 --> 31:59.458
- ** [ Clicking Continues ]
- ** [ Banjo ]

32:38.289 --> 32:41.291
[ Chattering In Distance ]

33:16.244 --> 33:18.245
[ Dog Barking In Distance ]

33:24.419 --> 33:27.421
*[ [ Piano: Scales ]

33:56.284 --> 33:58.243
- Listen, Carol. I — I —
- [ Vehicle Approaching ]

33:58.327 --> 34:00.704
- I don't —
- [ Horn Honks, Tires Screech ]
- [ Driver ] Clumsy bitch!

34:00.788 --> 34:02.706
For heaven's sake.

34:02.790 --> 34:04.916
- ** [ Up-tempoJazz ]
- Carol!

